1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:03,470
Your results are in, Ms. Monou.

2
00:00:03,470 --> 00:00:06,340
According to our diagnosis,

3
00:00:06,340 --> 00:00:08,720
you are infertile.

4
00:00:08,720 --> 00:00:10,720
I'm...

5
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:13,630
infertile?

6
00:00:13,630 --> 00:00:15,690
I wanted to stay with you forever, Sui.

7
00:00:15,690 --> 00:00:17,920
But when my parents saw your records...

8
00:00:17,920 --> 00:00:19,970
They told me the marriage was off.
[Diagnosis]

9
00:00:19,970 --> 00:00:21,250
If she's infertile,

10
00:00:21,250 --> 00:00:24,540
doesn't that mean you two can do it raw?

11
00:00:24,540 --> 00:00:25,600
That's a big win!

12
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:27,670
They're practically saying

13
00:00:27,670 --> 00:00:31,360
you've failed as a woman.

14
00:00:33,720 --> 00:00:35,730
Don't bother putting one on.

15
00:00:35,730 --> 00:00:38,830
I'll be fine.

16
00:00:38,830 --> 00:00:40,140
What are you talking about?

17
00:00:40,140 --> 00:00:43,330
These are for protecting your body.

18
00:00:53,060 --> 00:00:55,220
<i>Your door is now locked.</i>

19
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:01,660
Guess that wasn't all for us, huh?

20
00:01:04,220 --> 00:01:05,890
Thank you.

21
00:01:05,890 --> 00:01:08,490
That's all for us.

22
00:01:16,970 --> 00:01:19,350
Why are you...

23
00:01:19,350 --> 00:01:21,570
I live here.

24
00:01:21,570 --> 00:01:23,680
- Does that mean...
- <i>Your door is now locked.</i>

25
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:26,060
We're now neighbors, and coworkers.

26
00:01:26,060 --> 00:01:27,810
Welcome to the dorm.

27
00:01:30,580 --> 00:01:33,150
Don't be shocked.
You're the one who transferred in.

28
00:01:33,150 --> 00:01:34,690
What?

29
00:01:34,690 --> 00:01:38,750
I'm Erika's cousin, Mao Tsukidome.

30
00:01:38,750 --> 00:01:40,390
Nice to meet you.

31
00:01:42,470 --> 00:01:44,040
It's your first day, right?

32
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:46,730
Follow me.
I'll show you a shortcut to the office.

33
00:01:48,750 --> 00:01:50,530
Th-Thank you.

34
00:02:15,340 --> 00:02:18,160
Is this really happening?

35
00:03:29,390 --> 00:03:30,360
[Idea Construction Office]

36
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:35,230
This is Sui Monou, our newest team member.

37
00:03:35,230 --> 00:03:38,650
My name is Sui Monou.
It's nice to meet you all.

38
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:45,430
I'll have Mizuno and Mao teach you the ropes.

39
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:53,880
This is our cafe space.

40
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:57,170
You're free to take any of the drinks here.

41
00:03:57,170 --> 00:03:58,510
Thank you.

42
00:03:58,510 --> 00:04:01,640
This shelf is for our reference books,

43
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:04,450
and mail is to be placed here.

44
00:04:04,450 --> 00:04:05,940
I see.

45
00:04:05,940 --> 00:04:08,110
Mizuno. I'll take it from here.

46
00:04:08,110 --> 00:04:11,500
- Huh?
- I have plenty of work to explain.

47
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:13,410
- Follow me.
- Right.

48
00:04:13,410 --> 00:04:15,860
Thank you again.

49
00:04:15,860 --> 00:04:17,550
Take a seat.

50
00:04:22,570 --> 00:04:24,630
For starters,

51
00:04:24,630 --> 00:04:27,600
these are all the buildings
handled by our firm.

52
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:29,740
I see.

53
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:33,980
- You design hot springs as well?
- Yeah.

54
00:04:33,980 --> 00:04:36,000
It's an open air bath.

55
00:04:41,130 --> 00:04:43,340
What a cute store.

56
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:48,550
Thanks.

57
00:04:48,550 --> 00:04:50,800
I designed that one myself.

58
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,770
What?

59
00:04:52,770 --> 00:04:54,970
Mao's an officially licensed architect.

60
00:04:54,970 --> 00:04:56,940
He passed the exam on his first try.

61
00:04:56,940 --> 00:04:58,800
Really?

62
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,680
That's amazing.

63
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:03,780
I studied hard.

64
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:08,660
We passed these buildings on our way here.
Did you notice?

65
00:05:08,660 --> 00:05:10,200
What?

66
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:18,000
The shortcut doesn't save much time,

67
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,790
but it's a nicer view.

68
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:23,270
I see.

69
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:29,990
<i>What do you think of the night we shared?</i>

70
00:05:29,990 --> 00:05:33,050
<i>Why won't you ask me anything?</i>

71
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,230
<i>I certainly can't ask these questions now.</i>

72
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:43,770
What's up?

73
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:48,510
Sorry, it's nothing.

74
00:05:48,510 --> 00:05:50,110
If you insist.

75
00:05:51,380 --> 00:05:56,070
By the way, this is the building
we're handling right now.

76
00:06:09,810 --> 00:06:11,990
Oh.
[Memo]

77
00:06:13,110 --> 00:06:16,090
I write there when I can't find a notepad.

78
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:19,270
You must be glad it didn't fade away.

79
00:06:19,270 --> 00:06:20,780
Yeah.

80
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:27,610
I wonder if Monou is Mao's type.

81
00:06:27,610 --> 00:06:28,770
Huh?

82
00:06:28,770 --> 00:06:31,070
I mean, he's being extra kind to her.

83
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:36,420
You know that's just who Mao is.

84
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:40,920
Is that really all there is to it?

85
00:06:42,610 --> 00:06:47,990
Tsukidome. Thank you,
but I'll learn the rest on my own.

86
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,220
Just call me Mao.

87
00:06:51,220 --> 00:06:53,610
No formalities needed.

88
00:06:53,610 --> 00:06:56,680
You're the same age as Erika, right?

89
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:59,490
That means I'm several years your junior.

90
00:06:59,490 --> 00:07:01,710
Several? How old are you?

91
00:07:01,710 --> 00:07:03,610
I'm 26 years old.

92
00:07:05,250 --> 00:07:07,740
Six years my junior?

93
00:07:14,170 --> 00:07:15,930
Hello?

94
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:18,470
What?

95
00:07:18,470 --> 00:07:20,190
You found Sui?

96
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:21,350
Yes!

97
00:07:21,350 --> 00:07:23,560
Awesome.

98
00:07:24,700 --> 00:07:26,680
Where is she?

99
00:07:30,460 --> 00:07:32,420
Congrats on your first day!

100
00:07:32,420 --> 00:07:34,620
Cheers!

101
00:07:37,580 --> 00:07:39,400
That hits the spot.

102
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:42,760
So, how was it?

103
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:46,370
Everyone was so kind. I felt right at home.

104
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:49,840
Say...

105
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:51,380
Yeah?

106
00:07:53,620 --> 00:07:54,860
No, never mind.

107
00:07:54,860 --> 00:07:57,790
Now I'm extra curious.

108
00:08:00,490 --> 00:08:02,520
Well...

109
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:08,320
I thought I'd try to become
a licensed interior designer.

110
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:11,120
Great idea! You've got the eye for it,

111
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:14,520
so I always thought you should go for it.

112
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:16,990
This is all thanks to your introduction.

113
00:08:16,990 --> 00:08:19,530
I really can't thank you enough.

114
00:08:19,530 --> 00:08:21,910
It's my pleasure to help.

115
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:25,260
Mao's grown up, hasn't he?

116
00:08:26,420 --> 00:08:28,380
Huh? You don't remember him?

117
00:08:28,380 --> 00:08:30,570
You two met, long ago.

118
00:08:30,570 --> 00:08:32,620
- We did?
- Yeah.

119
00:08:32,620 --> 00:08:35,430
Back when he was in elementary school.

120
00:08:35,430 --> 00:08:38,600
Yeah, but I'm not sure.

121
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:42,340
Maybe I'm not confident enough...

122
00:08:43,020 --> 00:08:45,870
Hello there.

123
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:51,470
The kid who would always hid behind you?

124
00:08:51,470 --> 00:08:56,030
Yeah. He used to be such a downer.

125
00:08:58,850 --> 00:09:00,600
What about now?

126
00:09:01,670 --> 00:09:03,740
What's he like now?

127
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:10,140
No, it's not like that.

128
00:09:10,140 --> 00:09:11,730
Really now.

129
00:09:11,730 --> 00:09:14,100
I'm telling you, it's not.

130
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:15,830
I haven't said anything yet.

131
00:09:15,830 --> 00:09:19,040
Erika.

132
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:21,560
Stop that.

133
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:23,310
Jeez...

134
00:09:23,310 --> 00:09:25,420
I'm pulling your leg.

135
00:09:25,420 --> 00:09:27,860
Let's see...

136
00:09:27,860 --> 00:09:29,580
Now, he's a dude obsessed

137
00:09:29,580 --> 00:09:33,540
with helping people in need.

138
00:09:34,860 --> 00:09:36,860
I see.

139
00:09:38,790 --> 00:09:40,350
That reminds me.

140
00:09:41,820 --> 00:09:45,590
I got these from my relatives.
Take them with you.

141
00:09:45,590 --> 00:09:46,910
Hup.

142
00:09:46,910 --> 00:09:50,180
Never skimp on veggies,
even if you're living solo.

143
00:09:52,790 --> 00:09:54,590
This is a lot.

144
00:10:03,810 --> 00:10:05,460
I'll carry those.

145
00:10:05,460 --> 00:10:07,440
Thank you.

146
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:12,670
I'm sorry for causing you so much trouble.

147
00:10:12,670 --> 00:10:15,120
I'm just carrying your vegetables.

148
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:17,990
That's not the only "trouble"
I was referring to...

149
00:10:31,040 --> 00:10:32,940
- Here.
- Thank you.

150
00:10:34,890 --> 00:10:37,020
Good night.

151
00:10:37,020 --> 00:10:40,030
Thanks again. Good night.

152
00:10:45,940 --> 00:10:48,270
<i>Your door is now unlocked.</i>

153
00:10:50,520 --> 00:10:54,480
Maybe he is just nice.

154
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:59,440
<i>Your door is now unlocked.</i>

155
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:09,060
[Idea Construction Office]

156
00:11:09,060 --> 00:11:10,200
Sui.

157
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,430
Long time no see.

158
00:11:11,430 --> 00:11:12,990
Why are you here?

159
00:11:12,990 --> 00:11:14,700
I missed you.

160
00:11:14,700 --> 00:11:16,250
What?

161
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:21,140
You okay?

162
00:11:21,140 --> 00:11:22,640
Yeah.

163
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:27,800
Don't be such a stranger.

164
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:30,690
- We were engaged!
- And we have work to do.

165
00:11:30,690 --> 00:11:32,420
"We"?

166
00:11:35,610 --> 00:11:39,590
Himukai, you'll be late if you don't hurry.

167
00:11:50,130 --> 00:11:52,540
Fine. I'll leave for the day.

168
00:11:52,540 --> 00:11:55,940
Let's chat again some other time.

169
00:11:55,940 --> 00:11:57,540
See you!

170
00:12:05,390 --> 00:12:09,580
Thank you.

171
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:14,970
Arguing with the boyfriend first thing?

172
00:12:14,970 --> 00:12:16,970
Not appropriate, Matsubara.

173
00:12:16,970 --> 00:12:18,470
Right, sorry.

174
00:12:18,470 --> 00:12:22,150
Popular girls sure have it rough.

175
00:12:37,100 --> 00:12:39,260
We've drafted designs
for the Kawasaki branch,

176
00:12:39,260 --> 00:12:42,720
so could you choose flooring
and tables for the place?

177
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:45,290
I have a meeting now,

178
00:12:45,290 --> 00:12:46,850
but I'll check in with you tomorrow.

179
00:12:46,850 --> 00:12:50,700
- I'm excited to work with you.
- Likewise.

180
00:12:59,220 --> 00:13:02,560
Did you need something else?

181
00:13:04,540 --> 00:13:07,720
You seemed to be in a pinch this morning.

182
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:10,120
Was everything all right?

183
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:13,610
Yes. I'm sorry to worry you, Mizuno.

184
00:13:13,610 --> 00:13:14,760
Don't be.

185
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:18,640
I've dealt with a stalker before,

186
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:21,790
so I want to make sure you're careful.

187
00:13:21,790 --> 00:13:25,640
I don't think he's necessarily a stalker,

188
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:27,660
but I appreciate warning.

189
00:13:27,660 --> 00:13:29,520
Mizuno, ready to head out?

190
00:13:29,520 --> 00:13:31,880
Yup. Then I'll leave the rest to you.

191
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:33,470
Sure.

192
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:36,290
Ready?

193
00:13:50,150 --> 00:13:52,740
That's a new bracelet, isn't it?

194
00:13:52,740 --> 00:13:54,100
Oh, this?

195
00:13:57,080 --> 00:14:00,420
Was it a present from your girlfriend?

196
00:14:00,420 --> 00:14:03,070
If only.

197
00:14:03,070 --> 00:14:05,770
What? But...

198
00:14:15,140 --> 00:14:17,900
We've already been apart for two years now.

199
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:22,940
I'm gonna grab a drink. Want something?

200
00:14:22,940 --> 00:14:24,940
I'm fine, thank you.

201
00:14:24,940 --> 00:14:26,940
All right. I'll be right back.

202
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,740
A one-night stand?

203
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:44,600
[Family History]

204
00:14:48,770 --> 00:14:52,790
This herbal tea is great
for alleviating stress, and insomnia.

205
00:14:52,790 --> 00:14:54,700
Give it a try.

206
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:57,440
Thank you, Takizawa.

207
00:15:07,250 --> 00:15:12,570
I'm worried about you, Himukai.

208
00:15:14,020 --> 00:15:17,260
Sorry. I just can't forget about Sui.

209
00:15:18,140 --> 00:15:20,870
I know I'm the one who dumped her,

210
00:15:21,540 --> 00:15:25,150
but did she really have to act so cold?

211
00:15:25,150 --> 00:15:27,160
She's so cruel!

212
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:34,440
Don't worry, Himukai.

213
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:37,320
I have a brilliant idea, just for you.

214
00:15:39,950 --> 00:15:41,740
A brilliant idea?

215
00:15:43,020 --> 00:15:46,810
I also love Sui.

216
00:15:46,810 --> 00:15:50,910
And I want things to work out for you two.

217
00:15:50,910 --> 00:15:53,580
Always have.

218
00:15:55,020 --> 00:15:56,690
Really?

219
00:15:58,940 --> 00:16:01,210
Want to hear my brilliant scheme?

220
00:16:01,210 --> 00:16:07,650
It'll bring you two back together again.

221
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:13,030
A scheme, to bring us back together?

222
00:16:16,060 --> 00:16:19,110
[Monou]
[Ioka]

223
00:16:26,670 --> 00:16:30,560
I can't believe I used to live here.

224
00:16:34,110 --> 00:16:35,980
Cute, right?

225
00:16:35,980 --> 00:16:37,830
I gave them a quick rinse.

226
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:40,050
A rinse? Why?

227
00:16:40,770 --> 00:16:45,880
You're so clueless about pregnancy.

228
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:49,470
Even if they're new,
baby clothes need to be rinsed

229
00:16:49,470 --> 00:16:52,030
so the fabric doesn't irritate their skin.

230
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:57,130
Make sure you're taking notes for yourself.

231
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:01,730
I'll make us some tea.

232
00:17:01,730 --> 00:17:03,410
- How does black tea sound?
- Great, thanks.

233
00:17:04,290 --> 00:17:08,420
Just make sure it's the decaffeinated stuff.

234
00:17:10,550 --> 00:17:13,520
You're so conscious of your baby.

235
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:15,530
Of course. They're my child.

236
00:17:15,530 --> 00:17:18,430
You'll get it when your time comes, too.

237
00:17:18,430 --> 00:17:19,600
Think so?

238
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:21,870
Yeah, you will.

239
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:26,650
Are you not interested in having kids?

240
00:17:27,260 --> 00:17:29,020
That's not exactly it.

241
00:17:29,020 --> 00:17:33,050
Then you're better off knowing these things.

242
00:17:33,820 --> 00:17:37,110
How about we study up on pregnancy together?

243
00:17:43,910 --> 00:17:45,370
Sui.

244
00:17:46,310 --> 00:17:50,210
Are you thinking about your future?

245
00:17:50,210 --> 00:17:51,610
Huh?

246
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:57,750
I'm really happy with my life right now.

247
00:17:58,390 --> 00:18:02,280
That's why I want you to become happy, too.

248
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:05,710
I know you sacrificed a lot for me,

249
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:08,710
and you always put yourself second.

250
00:18:08,710 --> 00:18:10,360
Rin...

251
00:18:12,850 --> 00:18:15,240
Sui, be honest, am I the reason why

252
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:17,450
you broke off the engagement?

253
00:18:17,450 --> 00:18:19,300
What are you talking about?

254
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:21,240
You know that's not true.

255
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:23,150
But...

256
00:18:26,620 --> 00:18:30,750
Okay. Then you really are
thinking about your future?

257
00:18:30,750 --> 00:18:34,500
You haven't given up
on your own happiness, right?

258
00:18:38,830 --> 00:18:43,340
Of course not.
I changed jobs for that very reason.

259
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:54,210
Sui, I'm always here for you, okay?

260
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:59,860
Promise me you'll take your marriage
and future kids seriously.

261
00:19:09,380 --> 00:19:13,330
<i>Let's make sure our kids
become best friends, okay?</i>

262
00:19:13,330 --> 00:19:17,940
<i>They're practically saying
you've failed as a woman.</i>

263
00:19:17,940 --> 00:19:21,580
<i>I mean, infertile? After seven years together?</i>

264
00:19:21,580 --> 00:19:24,500
<i>You ought to be more wary. You're a woman.</i>

265
00:19:40,630 --> 00:19:43,160
Himukai?

266
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:45,380
Why are you...

267
00:19:45,380 --> 00:19:48,740
I'm sorry about the other day.
I wasn't in my right mind.

268
00:19:53,790 --> 00:19:56,840
But I want you to listen to me.

269
00:19:56,840 --> 00:20:00,130
I can't give up on you, Sui.

270
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:04,920
N-Not here.

271
00:20:23,170 --> 00:20:25,470
<i>Your door is now unlocked.</i>

272
00:20:28,320 --> 00:20:30,770
Thanks for having me.

273
00:20:41,570 --> 00:20:44,290
I'll convince my parents.

274
00:20:44,290 --> 00:20:46,930
I don't need any kids.

275
00:20:46,930 --> 00:20:49,210
Sui, you're the one who's important to me.

276
00:20:49,210 --> 00:20:50,920
You get that, right?

277
00:20:53,860 --> 00:20:55,650
Sui, I love you.

278
00:20:55,650 --> 00:20:57,110
Hey!

279
00:20:57,110 --> 00:20:58,880
What's wrong?

280
00:21:00,220 --> 00:21:01,970
We broke up.

281
00:21:01,970 --> 00:21:03,540
We broke up?

282
00:21:03,540 --> 00:21:05,740
But I still love you.

283
00:21:05,740 --> 00:21:09,350
You haven't been able to
forget me either, right?

284
00:21:13,230 --> 00:21:14,810
So, why...

285
00:21:14,810 --> 00:21:18,310
Why did you have to be infertile?

286
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:23,430
You messed everything up.

287
00:21:24,810 --> 00:21:27,000
Are you saying this is my fault?

288
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,500
But if marriage isn't on the table,

289
00:21:29,500 --> 00:21:32,530
I don't have to give up on you.

290
00:21:32,530 --> 00:21:36,590
- What?
- I said the marriage was off, sure.

291
00:21:36,590 --> 00:21:37,950
But I never said we'd break up.

292
00:21:37,950 --> 00:21:40,800
You want to stay with me too, don't you?

293
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:46,360
Even if I marry another woman,

294
00:21:46,360 --> 00:21:50,040
I can continue seeing you.

295
00:21:51,130 --> 00:21:52,170
You're not making any sense.

296
00:21:52,170 --> 00:21:55,900
Don't you get it? You dummy.

297
00:21:55,900 --> 00:22:00,330
I just can't have kids with you.

298
00:22:00,330 --> 00:22:03,390
Since you're infertile,
it'll work out perfectly.

299
00:22:29,740 --> 00:22:32,360
Come back to me, Sui.

300
00:22:33,610 --> 00:22:36,560
I'll process your company paperwork.

301
00:22:37,250 --> 00:22:38,980
Let's give this another shot.

302
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:42,990
No.

303
00:22:47,450 --> 00:22:50,900
Right, you're mad at me.

304
00:22:53,140 --> 00:22:56,540
I'm sorry I forced you to quit.

305
00:22:56,540 --> 00:22:58,740
But that was Mom and Dad's decision.

306
00:22:58,740 --> 00:23:01,680
So, forgive me, yeah?

307
00:23:06,180 --> 00:23:08,430
Don't worry.

308
00:23:08,430 --> 00:23:10,750
Making up is the easiest part.

309
00:23:10,750 --> 00:23:12,690
Get off.

310
00:23:12,690 --> 00:23:15,310
Don't touch me!

311
00:23:17,690 --> 00:23:21,790
You're the one who let me into your room.

312
00:23:21,790 --> 00:23:24,640
- Stop!
- Quit resisting already.

313
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:27,380
Stop, please!

314
00:23:27,380 --> 00:23:29,720
- Sui.
- Get off of her.

315
00:23:45,030 --> 00:23:47,150
Let's get married.

316
00:23:47,150 --> 00:23:50,570
I promise to bear a healthy heir for you.

317
00:23:50,570 --> 00:23:53,640
If you're anxious, I can stay here with you.

318
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:54,640
I'll be fine.

319
00:23:54,640 --> 00:23:56,370
Why?

320
00:23:56,370 --> 00:23:58,680
You don't have to ignore your resentment.

321
00:23:58,680 --> 00:23:59,800
Thank you.

